args:
When the unified force weakens Satan, Origa
chooses to seal herself and him away forever.
With the world saved, the people of Grams
begin to rebuild, and for the apostles, it's back
to their daily duties of administering Ilia's will.
Satan is reeling! Press the attack!
But not to flee. This is the same attack he\nused beforeâ€”I think he intends to wipe\nGrams out for good this time.
We can't reach him up there!
Her energy is surging! I've never seen\nanything like this!
It's beyond anything the rest of us could\nmuster. Perhaps the new Sigil has\nunlocked some latent potential in her?
It seems he expended all his power\nand returned to a stasis state.
Indeed it does. I shall use its power\nto separate Origa from Satan.
O crystal of purifying light, I bid you\nrelease the Auspex from the grasp of evil!
Sis...ter? Is this warmth...\ntruly your hand?
It is, Origa. And thank the Goddess I was\nable to take hold of yours this time.
I've been watching from inside the demon\nthis whole time and begging for it to end.\nIt was a nightmare.
Yet the destruction around me is no\ndream. I spoke of saving the world,\nbut now it lies broken by my own hand.
Forgive me. If I'd not been taken in\nby Loki's honeyed words...
The fault is mine alone. I knew it was a\nfoul choice I made, but my own weak\nheart lead me to trust in Satan's promise.
I understand the pull of hope you felt,\nhowever dark a form it took.
I myself once struggled in shadow,\ndoubting that others would lend an ear\nto my words.
Are you...the southern Auspex? If so,\nyou must be the prince of New Alberia.
That's me. It's good to finally meet you.
I would like to apologize for hounding you\nduring your time in Grams.

My actions were born of petty jealousyâ€”
jealously of your dragonblood and your
fortune in having been granted the power
to face your foes from birth.
That's all water under the bridge.\nWe share a common purpose now:\nto prevent the Progenitor's return.
The method you chose was wrong, but that\ndoesn't mean we can't keep fighting.
You are no longer the only one who sees\nthe threat of the Progenitor, Origa.\nAllies stand ready to join your cause.
You needn't toil alone anymore.\nYou can leave this in their hands.
So let us live together and atone\nfor all the harm we have done.
I'm sorry, Basileus. But I cannot do that.
My flesh has been separated from Satan,\nbut our souls remain tethered.

His exhaustion has granted me this brief
freedom, but he'll soon reel me back in.
And when that happens, he will awaken
once more.
No...! Is even the Sacred Shard's power\nnot enough to release you completely?!
Please, my fellow Auspex. You must use\nthe Shard's power to seal us both away.
NO! There has to be some other way.\nI'm your sister, and I'm going to save you.\nJust give me a little time!
Time is something I cannot grant you.\nBut you always were the smart one,\nand I think you knew that.
Satan is drawing her soul back into him.\nShe will be reabsorbed in moments.
Do not mourn, for this is a world\nripe with possibility.
This is but a brief farewell, my sister.\nYou will hold my hand in yours again.
I have steeled myselfâ€”please do not give\nme time to doubt my decision.
The Progenitor may arise while I am\nyet serving as Satan's yoke.
I leave that fight to you, and with it,\nthis world of beautiful possibility.
After Satan was sealed away once more,\nOriga's body alone remained.
Without a soul to animate it, she lay still, her\nskin growing hard as stone. And yet, the faint\nexpression on her face looked to be at peace.
I suppose you performed your duties\nwell enough to earn a single reprieve.
To think you would rescue me from \noblivion a second time, Your Highness.\nLong live Alberia's Prince Phares!
Or should I call you...the Progenitor?
Call me what you will. Still, it is a shame\nto see your lord sealed away yet again.
No sense crying over that. I've so many\ntoys left to play with, so I need only think\nup the rules of the next game.
And what of you, mmm? You desired\nSatan's revival as well, did you not?
So much so, in fact, that you broke my\nseal to bring it about.
The moment Satan was returned to this\nworld, my objective was accomplished.\nI care not what happened after.

And that objective is the resurrection of
your true form, yes? Can I then assume
that your return is near at hand?
How deliciously entertaining if so!
For you see, the world you seek to make\nsounds just catastrophically boring.
It will be quite the joy to crush it to pieces,\nso I shall see that the dawn of your new\nreality will also be its dusk.
I am, after all, a demon who delights in\nnothing more than seeing careful plans\nundone!
I'm afraid I won't permit that. This new\nworld will be my singular, perfect reality.
After Satan was sealed away, the people of Grams\nbegan to rebuild.
We're running low on building supplies.\nThink you can pull some strings?
I'll have a chat with a merchant I know\nand see what she is able to scrounge\ntogether.
Seeing men of such different stations\nwithin the Canon working hand in hand\nis something very new to Grams.
We still have our little grudges, Captain,\nbut we all want to see the city restored.
Satan's talons left a deep mark here.\nI only hope this will grant Grams a chance\nto be reborn better than before.

Speaking of, I hear there's big changes in
the works for the Church and government.
Sounds like those holy rollers might not be
calling the all the shots anymore?

Yes, it seems the government will be
charting a new course. Basel, who
supports the king, will lead the
reformation of the Church.
Our international affairs will no doubt\nchange as well.
New Alberia declared its support for Grams'\nrestoration, and their aid is destined to change the\nhistory of acrimony between the two kingdoms.
Here is the manifest of materials donated\nfrom Chanzelia. Can I ask you to deliver it\nto your king and Archbishop Basel?
I'll see that it reaches them.
Also, my little kittens tell me that there\nhave been dark rumblings among the\nnations bordering Grams.
Some of our neighbors weren't fond of\nGrams being the crown of the north for so\nlong. They may prefer us to remain in ruin.

Between the recovery efforts and
the threat of attack from outside,
the apostles will have no shortage
of work to keep them busy.

By the way, I'm told that Chanzelia's study
of ancient technology is second to none,
so what would you say to a research
exchange?
Is this an official request on behalf\nof Grams?
More of a personal request. Origa's body\nis in a state of stasis, but ifâ€”WHENâ€”her\nsoul is retrieved, she can still be saved.
I'm going to find a way to free her soul\nfrom Satan and bring her back.
I shall bend my will to this task as well.\nPerhaps Metatron's past research might\noffer some clue.
Well, I HAVE had my eye on the alchemy\nrecipes said to be collecting dust in the\nChurch's vaults for a while now...
I can't help but wonder what might have been if\nGrams and New Alberia had found themselves on\nbetter terms from the start.
Maybe Origa could have consulted with the prince\nor Zena about the Progenitor.
Basileus and Michael's punishment for conspiring\nwith Origa was left pending, so they began working\nas apostle and angel once more.
Apparently the Church determined that they\ncouldn't afford to leave any tactical assets\noff the table in such unstable times.
Once Grams is in a better place,\nthey'll be formally tried for their crimes.
Yes. I suppose it's nearly time, mmm?\nLet's hurry to the others.
And Michael? Thank you in advance\nfor whatever moments we have left.
Once your sentencing comes, I'll be made\nto form a Sigil with a new apostle\ncandidate they've readied.
But I will treasure each day I get to spend\nwith you until then.
Any word of what Harle has been up to?
He said he'd go back to working solo for\na whileâ€”apparently Loki wasn't the only\none who conspired to seal him away.
He did promise to drop in from time\nto time to share information, though.
Is he the sort who avoids getting too close\nto others?
I'm not so sure. Leif and Cecile seem\neager to reunite with him.
So what about you? Have you found any\ntraces of the Five Archdemons?
No. It seems they've gone underground\nonce more.
The moment Satan was sealed, the Archdemons\nwho were rampaging across the land vanished.
Nrgh?! My link to Satan has been cut!
Well, THAT is a total buzzkill. Guess I'll\nblow this joint for now.
Bye for now, meat! Oh, but I'll be back to\nplay with you again real soon, so you can\nabsolutely look forward to that.
We'll have to deal with them again.\nI'm sure of it.
Metatron was convinced we were capable\nof handling them.
And this time, we don't just seal them off.\nInstead, we find a way to eliminate the\npack of them once and for all.
And when that battle comes,\nyou'll have us at your side.
I promised Origa that the Progenitor\nwould not be revived, and I intend to\nkeep that vow!
Time for work, Pi. The others are waiting.
Uh oh, Pi. Your hair is sticking up again.\nHere, let Mama fix that for you.
Leave it, Gabriel! I am not a...\nEr, well, I suppose it's all right.
Hee hee! That's my Little Pi.
Awfully relaxed for the pair who arrived\nlate to the briefing.
Oh, hush. Watching those two fuss over\neach other takes the edge off for all of us.
Yet tardiness is tardiness still. I'm docking\npoints for failing to remember her\nresponsibilities as an apostle.
After shooting Satan out of the heavens,\nPinon is our ace apostle.
Then she would do well to comport herself\nwith a dignity befitting the role.
Eh, leave her alone. She'll always be that\nadorable little rookie to me.
If you wish to play the grown-up, Nevin,\nyou might consider cleaning your room\nat some point.
I call you all to order.
We have a new mission from Basel.\nThough Grams is scarcely back on its feet,\na new threat looms on the horizon.
You are to quell it so her people can\nwork in peace to build a new home\nrich with possibility.
Understood! I am the apostle Pinon,\none hand of the Goddess, and I shall\nsee Her will done!
